---
import BadgeShine from "@/components/BadgeShine.astro";
import Github from "@/components/logos/Github.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import logos from "@/logos";

const technologies = [
  logos.NEXTJS,
  logos.TYPESCRIPT,
  logos.TAILWIND,
  logos.SUPABASE,
  logos.PRISMA,
]

const images = [
  "/portfolio-web/images/pomodoro_totoro_gallery/about_section.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/pomodoro_totoro_gallery/edit_mode.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/pomodoro_totoro_gallery/login.webp",
  "/portfolio-web/images/pomodoro_totoro_gallery/register.webp",
]
---

<Layout title="User Administration Table" desc="Details about the User Admin. Table project!">
  <section class="pt-40 pb-40 w-full md:w-9/12 mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-5 underline">Pomodoro Totoro</h1>
    
    <nav class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-y-5 w-fit gap-x-4 text-wrap mb-5">
      <BadgeShine class="flex flex-row gap-x-2 pointer-events-auto" href="https://github.com/JoelFaldin/pomodoro-totoro">
        <Github class="size-6" />
        Github
      </BadgeShine>
      <BadgeShine class="flex flex-row gap-x-2 pointer-events-auto" href="https://pomodoro-totoro.vercel.app">
        <Github class="size-6" />
        Demo
      </BadgeShine>
    </nav>

    <article class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-x-10 pb-14">
      <section class="w-full lg:w-2/5 text-wrap flex flex-col gap-y-2">
        <p>I built this project inspired on the Pomodoro Technique!</p>
        <p>The project consists on a timer that makes a sound when it reaches 0. I wanted to take things one step further, so I implemented a <span class="text-cyan-500">custom login system</span> and auth with Github and Google.</p>
        <p>I also implemented a functionality to <span class="text-cyan-500">upload an audio file</span> to play when you log in. Supabase worked like charm with this!</p>
        <p>(But some times, Supabase turns off the audio storage ðŸ˜“ and I need to manually turn it on.)</p>
        <p>Another reason I had to build this project was to learn the basics of <a href="https://nextjs.org" class="text-cyan-500 hover:underline">NextJS</a>. I had a lot of fun too!</p>

        <p class="mt-5 text-xl">Technologies used:</p>

        <ul class="flex gap-x-4 flex-row mt-2 mb-2">
          {
            technologies.map(logo => (
              <li>
                <logo.icon class="size-8" />
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section class="w-3/5">
        <img
          src="/portfolio-web/images/pomodoro_totoro_landpage.webp"
          alt="Main view of the User Administration project"
          height="350"
          width="700"
          class="shadow-xl border border-cyan-500 h-72 w-auto md:h-[350px] min-w-fit"
        >
      </section>
    </article>

    <article class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">More images:</h2>

      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 xl:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-8">
        {
          images.map(pic => (
            <img
              src={pic}
              height="300"
              width="600"
              class="w-fit shadow-2xl"
              alt="Image examples of the React User Administration project"
            />
          ))
        }
      </section>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>